          "title": "马里兰大学等机构研究：AI模型学会「局部改稿」，反射性遮蔽技术突破",
          "title_en": "University of Maryland Research: AI Models Learn \"Local Revision\" with Reflective Masking Breakthrough",
          "summary": "马里兰大学等机构联合研究发布新方法，让AI模型具备「局部改稿」能力——像人一样只修改有问题的段落，其他部分完好保留。",
          "summary_en": "University of Maryland and partners release research enabling AI models with \"local revision\" capability — like humans, only modifying problematic sections while preserving others.",
          "source": "头条",
          "source_en": "Toutiao",
          "image": "img/pool/education-tutoring.jpg",
          "content": "马里兰大学、弗吉尼亚理工大学、Intuit、加州大学戴维斯分校和阿布扎比穆罕默德·本·扎耶德人工智能大学联合开展的研究，于2026年6月以预印本形式发布。\n\n当前主流的AI文字生成系统有一个根本性局限：它们从左到右逐词生成，一旦写出来的内容有问题，就得把后面所有内容全部推倒重来。研究团队找到了一种方法，让特定类型的AI模型真正学会「局部改稿」的能力。\n\n研究团队将激活这种主动自我修正能力的方法命名为「反射性遮蔽」（Reflective Masking）。其核心思想是：要求模型不仅能填空，还能主动判断「我现在还认为这个词是对的吗？」如果不对，就重新打上MASK标记，让自己再预测一次。\n\n为了解决反复改同一个错误的问题，研究团队引入了「历史参考」（History Reference）机制——在每次做出「保留还是遮蔽」的决策时，模型不仅能看到当前的序列状态，还能感知到这个位置在过去几步的变化历史。\n\n这意味着AI正在从「一次成型」向「迭代优化」进化，更接近人类写作的思维方式。",
          "content_en": "A joint research effort by the University of Maryland, Virginia Tech, Intuit, UC Davis, and Mohamed bin Zayed University of AI released findings as a preprint in June 2026.\n\nCurrent mainstream AI text generation systems have a fundamental limitation: they generate left-to-right, word-by-word, and if something is wrong, everything after must be regenerated. The research team found a way to enable AI models to truly learn \"local revision\" capability.\n\nThe team named this method for activating proactive self-correction \"Reflective Masking.\" Its core idea: requiring models not only to fill in blanks but to actively judge \"Do I still think this word is correct?\" If not, reapply MASK and predict again.\n\nTo solve the problem of repeatedly making the same error, the team introduced a \"History Reference\" mechanism — when making \"keep or mask\" decisions, the model can see not only the current sequence state but also sense the position's change history over recent steps.\n\nThis means AI is evolving from \"one-shot generation\" toward \"iterative optimization,\" more closely matching human writing thinking.",
