          "title": "GitHub 21k星！AirLLM：单卡4GB显存跑70B大模型重新定义LLM推理",
          "title_en": "GitHub 21k Stars! AirLLM: Run 70B Models on 4GB GPU Revolutionizes LLM Inference",
          "summary": "AirLLM通过分层加载技术让普通显卡也能跑70B大模型，无需量化、不需蒸馏，4GB显存即可运行，降低大模型推理门槛。",
          "summary_en": "AirLLM enables consumer GPUs to run 70B models through layer-wise loading without quantization or distillation, requiring only 4GB VRAM, democratizing large model inference.",
          "source": "牛码架构",
          "source_en": "NiuMa Architecture",
          "image": "img/pool/opensource-workshop.jpg",
          "content": "AirLLM是一个让你在消费级GPU上跑超大参数模型的推理框架。核心卖点：不需要量化、不需要蒸馏、不需要剪枝，一张4GB显存的显卡就能跑70B参数的LLM。如果显卡稍微好点，8GB显存更是能跑Llama 3.1 405B。\n\n项目已在GitHub拿下21K+星，解决的是大模型推理的门槛问题：70B模型正常加载需要140GB+显存，405B模型更是要800GB+，普通开发者和中小企业根本玩不起。\n\nAirLLM的核心思路很巧妙：大模型推理的瓶颈主要在显存而不是算力。传统方式是把整个模型一次性加载到GPU显存，而AirLLM把模型按层拆分，每次只加载一层所需的权重到GPU，计算完成后卸载，再加载下一层。\n\n这种方案有几个关键优势：显存占用极低（峰值≈单层参数量）、无需量化（保持完整精度）、兼容主流模型（Llama、ChatGLM、Qwen、Baichuan、Mistral、InternLM等）。\n\nv2.0还引入了基于分块量化的模型压缩技术，可将推理速度提升3倍，精度损失几乎可以忽略不计。",
          "content_en": "AirLLM is an inference framework allowing consumer GPUs to run super large parameter models. Core selling point: no quantization, no distillation, no pruning — 4GB VRAM can run 70B parameter LLMs. With slightly better GPUs, 8GB can run Llama 3.1 405B.\n\nThe project has garnered 21K+ stars on GitHub, solving the barrier to large model inference: 70B models normally require 140GB+ VRAM, 405B models need 800GB+, unaffordable for regular developers and SMEs.\n\nAirLLM's clever approach: large model inference bottlenecks are primarily in VRAM not compute. Traditional methods load entire models into GPU VRAM at once, while AirLLM splits models by layer, loading only one layer's weights at a time, then unloading and loading the next.\n\nKey advantages: extremely low VRAM usage (peak ≈ single layer parameters), no quantization (maintains full precision), compatible with mainstream models (Llama, ChatGLM, Qwen, Baichuan, Mistral, InternLM, etc.).\n\nVersion 2.0 introduces block-wise quantization for model compression, boosting inference speed 3x with negligible accuracy loss.",
