          "image": "img/pool/ai-customer-service.jpg",
          "content": "高通与全球最大AI开源社区Hugging Face宣布扩大合作伙伴关系，共同推进跨设备到云环境的开放、开发者驱动的人工智能发展。\n\n根据新合作协议，高通将持续为开发者提供工具与基础设施，支持AI模型在端侧与云端双轨运行。高通AI Hub支持TensorFlow Lite、ONNX Runtime及Qualcomm AI Engine等主流框架，开发者可一次开发、多端部署。\n\n此举标志着端侧AI推理的生态加速——随着骁龙芯片AI算力持续提升，越来越多大模型能力将从云端下沉至手机、PC等终端设备运行，降低延迟、保护隐私、减少云端依赖。\n\n这也是Hugging Face继与亚马逊、谷歌云合作后，又一大硬件平台合作，开源AI模型从云端优先向端云协同的演进趋势愈发清晰。",
          "content_en": "Qualcomm and Hugging Face, the world's largest AI open source community, announced an expanded partnership to jointly advance open, developer-driven AI development across device-to-cloud environments.\n\nUnder the new agreement, Qualcomm continues providing developers with tools and infrastructure supporting AI models running both on-device and in the cloud. Qualcomm AI Hub supports TensorFlow Lite, ONNX Runtime, and Qualcomm AI Engine, enabling developers to build once and deploy everywhere.\n\nThis marks acceleration of on-device AI inference ecosystems — as Snapdragon chip AI computing power increases, more large model capabilities move from cloud to mobile phones, PCs, and other endpoints, reducing latency, protecting privacy, and minimizing cloud dependency.\n\nThis is also Hugging Face's latest major hardware platform partnership following collaborations with Amazon and Google Cloud, with the trend of open source AI evolving from cloud-first to device-cloud collaboration becoming increasingly clear.",
