          "image": "img/pool/deep-analysis-research.jpg",
          "content": "36氪发布深度分析文章，系统梳理2026年AI从chatbot到agent的范式转移。\n\n核心发现：chatbot赛道增量已逼近天花板。AI产品榜数据显示，2026年4月chatbot榜单TOP20中9大产品网站访问量出现下滑，ChatGPT虽以5.69亿访问量领先但环比负增长3.84%。\n\n而Claude逆势增长34.18%，原因在于完成了从被动问答chatbot到主动代劳agent的范式转移。Claude Co-Work功能可跨软件长流程全自动执行，高频自动化交互直接推高Token消耗和访问量。\n\n资本市场转向更为彻底：a16z持续多轮押注编程agent Cursor，红杉投资智能客服agent Sierra，Coatue投资企业客服agent Decagon。国内，阿里、腾讯等大厂也已将资源整合，投向自身agent能力搭建。\n\nYC W26约200家创业公司中，大量AI项目重心在agent而非chatbot。这一变化表明：chatbot越来越成为平台生态中的基础能力，而非独立的创业赛道。",
          "content_en": "36Kr published in-depth analysis systematically reviewing AI's paradigm shift from chatbot to agent in 2026.\n\nKey finding: chatbot growth has hit a ceiling. AI Product Index data shows 9 of top 20 chatbot products saw declining website traffic in April 2026, with ChatGPT's 569 million visits showing -3.84% month-over-month decline.\n\nClaude bucked the trend with 34.18% growth, driven by completing the paradigm shift from passive Q&A chatbot to proactive agent. Claude Co-Work enables cross-software, long-process fully autonomous execution, with high-frequency automated interactions directly driving token consumption and visit growth.\n\nCapital market pivot is decisive: a16z continues multi-round bets on coding agent Cursor, Sequoia invests in customer service agent Sierra, Coatue funds enterprise customer service agent Decagon. Domestically, Alibaba, Tencent, and other major players have consolidated resources toward their own agent capability development.\n\nAt YC W26, among ~200 startups, many AI projects focus on agents rather than chatbots. This change indicates: chatbots are increasingly becoming basic capabilities within platform ecosystems rather than independent entrepreneurial tracks.",
